- Current status implies the latest available information; 
- Number of documents refers to the total count of documents within a project;
- Latest document version refers to the highest version number of documents in a project;
- Number of sensors assigned refers to the count of unique sensors allocated to a project;
- Most recent activity refers to the latest log event date for a project;
- Average user access duration refers to the mean time users spend accessing a project.

- The term 'recent' refers to events that occurred in the last month; 
- 'Details of recent measurements' include measurement IDs, project names, sensor names, and sensor types; 
- 'Recent accesses' include the users who last accessed the projects and the dates of the last accesses; 
- 'Recent log events' include the descriptions of the most recent log events for each project.

sql:
SELECT doc_title, file_size
FROM project_documents
WHERE file_size = (SELECT MAX(file_size) FROM project_documents);

